  "prompt": "What is a speech?",
  "response": "A speech is a formal address or discourse delivered to an audience. It typically aims to inform, persuade, motivate, or entertain the listeners. Speeches can vary widely in context and style, from political addresses and academic lectures to wedding toasts and motivational talks. The effectiveness of a speech often depends on its content, the delivery style of the speaker, and the engagement with the audience. Key elements of a good speech generally include a clear message, a logical structure, appropriate language and tone, and the ability to connect with the audience emotionally or intellectually.",
